The former Lagos Governor made this known on Monday during his campaign rally in Yola, Adamawa State capital. The presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu, has vowed to end the incessant killings and kidnapping under the present President Muhammadu Buhari’s government in Nigeria if elected as the country’s president in February.
The former Lagos Governor made this known on Monday during his campaign rally in Yola, Adamawa State capital.
“There will be end to killing and kidnapping,” he promised.
Tinubu also promised to provide jobs for youths, facilitate adequate healthcare, good education amongst other “benefits of progress” if elected.
Tinubu was at the rally alongside APC stakeholders including President Muhammadu Buhari and the party’s governorship candidate for Adamawa, Aisha Ahmed popularly called Binani.
General elections will be held in Nigeria on 25 February 2023 to elect the President and Vice President and members of the Senate and House of Representatives.
The APC presidential candidate added that his party did not have only men but also “capable women” even as he urged the party’s supporter to vote in Binani.
“We will get you engaged properly, we will get you employed properly,” Tinubu told the party’s supporters at the rally.
“We will pay attention to your needs, with Binani working together with the President, Bola Tinubu insha Allah (by God’s grace), we will bring you the benefits of progress, education, good health, welfare, you will have good water to drink. There will be end to killing and kidnapping.”